  "prompt": "Which country invented the sandwich?",
  "response": "The invention of the sandwich is commonly attributed to John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich, in England. The story goes that in the 18th century, Montagu requested his servant to bring him meat tucked between two pieces of bread so he could eat without interrupting his gambling game. This convenient method of eating became popular and was thus named after him. While similar food combinations may have existed prior to this, the concept of the modern sandwich as we know it today is generally credited to England.",
